<title>USA: HMT to spend $200 mln in '98 to up output.</title>
<headline>HMT to spend $200 mln in '98 to up output.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-07-29</dateline>
<text>
<p>HMT Technology Corp said Tuesday it currently expects to spend in excess of $200 million during calendar year 1998 to expand its production capacity.</p>
<p>HMT, which makes thin film disks for hard disk drives, said a substantial majority of the amount will be spent on its Fremont, Calif., facility.</p>
<p>In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission, HMT said that it invested $39.8 million and $21.7 million in property, plant and equipment during its first fiscal quarter ended June 30, 1997 and 1996, respectively.</p>
